# /agent-create — Criar Agente LLM

## Uso
```
/agent-create [nome]
```

## Conceito

Agentes sao pipelines LLM com prompts estruturados, tools, e endpoints de exposicao. Combinam regras deterministicas com capacidades de LLM.

## Fases

### Fase 0 — Reconhecimento
1. Ler agentes existentes para entender o padrao
2. Identificar tools disponiveis
3. Verificar regras deterministicas relacionadas
{{#if stack}}
4. Ler padroes da stack em [patterns.md](patterns.md)
{{/if}}

### Fase 1 — Prompt
- **System prompt**: Define papel, restricoes, formato de saida
- **Template de input**: Estruturado com dados de contexto
- **Structured output**: Schema de resposta do LLM
- **Exemplos**: Few-shot quando necessario

### Fase 2 — Pipeline
- Pre-processamento de dados de entrada
- Chamada LLM com prompt construido
- Parsing de resposta estruturada
- Pos-processamento e validacao

### Fase 3 — Tools
- Registrar tools que o agente pode usar
- Cada tool com docstring descritiva
- Tratar fallback quando tool falha

### Fase 4 — Endpoint
- Expor agente via API (REST ou MCP)
- Schema de request/response
- Timeout e retry configurados
- Observabilidade (tokens, custo, latencia)

### Fase 5 — Testes
- Testar com inputs validos
- Testar structured output parsing
- Testar fallback de tools
- Testar timeout e erros
- Mock de LLM para testes rapidos

## Checklist
- [ ] System prompt claro e com restricoes
- [ ] Structured output com schema
- [ ] Tools com docstrings descritivas
- [ ] Observabilidade (tokens/custo/latencia)
- [ ] Timeout e retry configurados
- [ ] Testes com LLM mockado
- [ ] Endpoint documentado
{{else}}
# /agent-create — Create LLM Agent

## Usage
```
/agent-create [name]
```

## Concept

Agents are LLM pipelines with structured prompts, tools, and exposure endpoints. They combine deterministic rules with LLM capabilities.

## Phases

### Phase 0 — Reconnaissance
1. Read existing agents to understand the pattern
2. Identify available tools
3. Check related deterministic rules
{{#if stack}}
4. Read stack patterns in [patterns.md](patterns.md)
{{/if}}

### Phase 1 — Prompt
- **System prompt**: Defines role, constraints, output format
- **Input template**: Structured with context data
- **Structured output**: LLM response schema
- **Examples**: Few-shot when necessary

### Phase 2 — Pipeline
- Pre-process input data
- LLM call with constructed prompt
- Structured response parsing
- Post-processing and validation

### Phase 3 — Tools
- Register tools the agent can use
- Each tool with descriptive docstring
- Handle fallback when tool fails

### Phase 4 — Endpoint
- Expose agent via API (REST or MCP)
- Request/response schema
- Timeout and retry configured
- Observability (tokens, cost, latency)

### Phase 5 — Tests
- Test with valid inputs
- Test structured output parsing
- Test tool fallback
- Test timeout and errors
- LLM mock for fast tests

## Checklist
- [ ] Clear system prompt with constraints
- [ ] Structured output with schema
- [ ] Tools with descriptive docstrings
- [ ] Observability (tokens/cost/latency)
- [ ] Timeout and retry configured
- [ ] Tests with mocked LLM
- [ ] Endpoint documented
{{/if}}
